<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11124b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11124b">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11124b"> 124(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Nicolas Morbus / a ta sant&eacute; Morbus / corbillard ici</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">J&apos;ai vu des ivrognes &agrave; la barri&egrave;re, assis devant la porte du cabaret, buvant sur une petite table de bois et disant en &eacute;levant leur verre: <mark>&ldquo;A ta sant&eacute;, Morbus!&rdquo;</mark> Morbus, par reconnaissaice, accourait, et ils tombaient morts sous la table. Les enfants jouaient au <i>chol&eacute;ra</i>, qu&apos;ils appelaient le <mark>Nicolas Morbus</mark> et le sc&eacute;l&eacute;rat Morbus. &hellip; Dans la rue de S&egrave;vres, compl&egrave;tement d&eacute;vast&eacute;e, surtout d&apos;un c&ocirc;t&eacute;, les corbillards allaient et venaiet de porte en porte; ils ne pouvaien suffire aux demandes; on leur cirait par les fen&ecirc;tres: <mark>&ldquo;Corbillard, ici!&rdquo;</mark> <br><font color="green">[I saw drunkards at the gate, seated before the tavern door, drinking at a small wooden table and saying as they raised their glasses: &ldquo;Here&apos;s to your health, Morbus!&rdquo; Morbus gratefully rushed up, and they fell dead beneath the table. The children played at cholera, which they called &lsquo;Nicolas Morbus&rsquo; and &lsquo;villainous Morbus.&rsquo; [...]</font> In the Rue de Se&egrave;vres, which was completely ravaged, especially on one side, the hearses came and went from door to door; they could not keep up with the demand. People shouted to them through the windows: &ldquo;Hearse over here!&rdquo;] <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> [<b>Le Chole&eacute;ra</b>] ]160</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
